{
  "texts": [
    "Still, even if the resulting DCT specifications end up just describing how a team of researchers decided to \"fill in blanks\" in the construct definitions in the original theory formulation, that would provide valuable context to other researchers.",
    "The multiple theories approach consists of conducting a systematic review of primary sources of various theories.",
    "This results in a comprehensive overview of theoretical contributions.",
    "For such an overview to be comprehensive, the search strategy should not be focused on specific theories, but on the psychological construct of interest.",
    "A benefit similar to the single theory approach is the direct link between the construct definitions and instructions on how to use them in research (if they are specified)."
  ]
}